Reproduction of the field: Attracting students and sustaining training amid broader pressures on the humanities/social sciences.

Overall, medical anthropology is thriving as a theoretically rich, empirically grounded, and increasingly relevant field. It offers unique “thick” insights into why health interventions succeed or fail and how health is lived and governed in context. For the latest, follow SMA resources, the journals above, and sites like Somatosphere. Primary ethnographies and recent handbooks/companion volumes provide deeper empirical grounding. The landscape is more global, collaborative, and engaged with urgent crises than ever before."

